        <h2>Where JobTread wins</h2>

        <h3>Job costing: JobTread's standout strength</h3>
        <p>JobTread's real-time job costing is the feature that turns contractors into advocates. As you create purchase orders, log expenses, and track labor, you see budget vs. actual updating in real time — not at month-end when it's too late to course-correct.</p>

        <p>The committed cost model is particularly strong: when you create a PO for materials, that amount is "committed" immediately — even before the invoice arrives — so your budget view reflects what you've agreed to spend, not just what you've paid. This is the difference between knowing your margin and guessing it.</p>

        <ul>
          <li>Real-time budget vs. actual by cost code</li>
          <li>Committed costs from POs before invoices arrive</li>
          <li>Job margin dashboard across all active projects</li>
          <li>Direct connection from estimate line items to cost tracking buckets</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Pricing: JobTread is 5x cheaper to start</h3>
        <p>At $99/month with unlimited users, JobTread is accessible to contractors who aren't yet ready for Buildertrend's $499/month entry point. For a single-crew contractor doing $800K/year, the price difference is material — and JobTread delivers genuine value at that tier.</p>

        <h3>Ease of adoption</h3>
        <p>JobTread has a cleaner, more modern UI than Buildertrend in several areas. New users often get productive faster — there's less to learn before the software starts paying for itself.</p>

        <h2>Where Buildertrend wins</h2>

        <h3>Selections management</h3>
        <p>For custom homebuilders managing hundreds of owner selections — flooring, fixtures, cabinet hardware, appliance models — Buildertrend's selections module is more complete than JobTread's. It tracks allowances, collects client approvals, and creates a timestamped paper trail for every selection decision.</p>

        <h3>Client portal depth</h3>
        <p>Buildertrend's homeowner portal is among the best in the industry. It's clean, mobile-friendly, and gives clients real visibility — which reduces the "how's my project going?" calls dramatically. JobTread has a client portal, but it's less polished.</p>

        <h3>Scheduling sophistication</h3>
        <p>Buildertrend's Gantt scheduler handles complex dependencies and automatically cascades schedule changes downstream. For builders managing 20+ concurrent projects with multi-trade schedules, this matters.</p>

        <h3>Ecosystem and integrations</h3>
        <p>Buildertrend has 10+ years of integrations — QuickBooks, Xero, DocuSign, BuildingConnected, and more — and a larger community of consultants and trained users. If your team needs to find people who know the software, Buildertrend has a larger talent pool.</p>

        <h2>The honest take: who should choose JobTread</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Contractors under $2M revenue for whom $499/month feels like a stretch</li>
          <li>Contractors who've been burned by poor job costing — margin is the priority</li>
          <li>Teams that want a clean, fast platform that doesn't take months to master</li>
          <li>Remodelers and specialty contractors who don't need complex selections management</li>
        </ul>

