        </ul>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <p><strong>Buildertrend is the market standard for residential builders with good reason.</strong></p>
          <a href="https://www.buildertrend.com" rel="nofollow sponsored" class="btn">Try Buildertrend</a>
        </div>

        <h2>The verdict</h2>
        <p>JobTread is the right choice if your primary pain point is job costing and you're not yet at the scale where Buildertrend's feature depth justifies the price. Buildertrend is worth the investment when you're managing complex projects with engaged homeowners, extensive selections, and a team that needs a mature, feature-complete platform.</p>

        <p>Many contractors start with JobTread and graduate to Buildertrend as their business scales. That's a reasonable path — both tools export your data.</p>

